WEBVTT

00:56.014 --> 00:57.974
What did you do?!

01:32.676 --> 01:34.511
<i>Harriet Jacobs writes,</i>

01:34.552 --> 01:36.721
<i>"I was born a slave,</i>
<i>but I never knew it</i>

01:36.805 --> 01:40.308
<i>till six years of happy</i>
<i>childhood had passed away."</i>

01:41.184 --> 01:43.895
I think what's interesting
is how Ms. Jacobs

01:43.937 --> 01:46.731
ignited the compassion
for those still in bondage,

01:46.815 --> 01:49.401
exciting Northern white women
and men -

01:49.484 --> 01:51.027
with the plight
of the slave girl.

01:51.069 --> 01:52.320
So...

01:54.280 --> 01:57.826
Shay, can you please control
your environment?

02:00.745 --> 02:01.913
Jasmine.

02:03.081 --> 02:05.750
My bad.

02:07.002 --> 02:08.003
All right,

02:08.086 --> 02:09.963
let's wrap it up here for today.

02:10.046 --> 02:12.173
Next week, you'll be discussing
Paul Laurence Dunbar's poem

02:12.257 --> 02:14.551
- "Sympathy"...
- Yeah.

02:14.592 --> 02:17.178
So, uh...

02:17.262 --> 02:18.304
right now?

02:18.388 --> 02:19.764
This early, hmm?

02:21.266 --> 02:22.726
In the morning, it's medicine.

02:24.102 --> 02:27.439
Just not while
I'm in class, okay?

02:29.649 --> 02:30.608
Still pending?

02:30.650 --> 02:33.570
-Still pending.
-Shit.

02:33.611 --> 02:36.906
-All of them?
-Yep.

02:36.948 --> 02:38.575
Everything slowed down.

02:38.616 --> 02:41.745
And the center cut my hours.

02:41.786 --> 02:43.788
Well, don't worry.

02:43.872 --> 02:46.875
I got my financial aid
coming in next month, so...

02:46.958 --> 02:49.169
Mm, nice for you.

02:49.252 --> 02:51.338
Gold Grant withheld mine.

02:51.421 --> 02:53.590
So what's the point
of Gold Grant then

02:53.631 --> 02:55.800
if we can't even get
the classes that we need?

02:55.884 --> 02:57.302
I'm only taking one class,

02:57.344 --> 03:00.430
and they didn't offer one
I needed to transfer.

03:00.472 --> 03:02.599
Let's get out of here and move
to Atlanta or something.

03:02.640 --> 03:06.561
I mean, realistically, neither
of us can afford to move.

03:06.644 --> 03:08.855
Because we are big broke.

03:10.690 --> 03:14.235
The beauty of being broke

03:14.319 --> 03:16.488
is that we can
be broke anywhere.

03:17.530 --> 03:19.532
You hear me?

03:20.325 --> 03:22.494
I'm serious, Shay.

03:22.535 --> 03:24.621
What's keeping you here?

04:15.880 --> 04:16.965
Shay?

04:17.007 --> 04:19.217
Oh, I'm so glad I caught you.

04:19.259 --> 04:21.219
Hi. I'm Kate Simmons.

04:21.261 --> 04:22.929
Uh, hi.

04:24.305 --> 04:25.974
Sorry, am I
supposed to know you?

04:26.057 --> 04:28.643
Oh, um, I got your application
on Sitter Search.

04:28.727 --> 04:30.186
-Oh.
-And I read your bio.

04:30.228 --> 04:31.604
I checked all your references.

04:31.688 --> 04:33.440
It turns out
I know your boss Christopher.

04:33.523 --> 04:35.316
We went to high school together.

04:35.400 --> 04:38.403
I was just here
asking about you.

04:39.612 --> 04:42.240
So, uh, which listing were you?

04:42.282 --> 04:44.868
It's the Hopkins estate.

04:44.909 --> 04:46.661
Here.

04:52.208 --> 04:54.336
Yeah, I, uh...

04:54.419 --> 04:55.712
I know this place.

04:55.754 --> 04:57.839
I know it's not
the most colorful photo,

04:57.922 --> 05:00.592
but, uh, it's not
a plantation anymore.

05:00.633 --> 05:02.218
It's been in the family
for generations.

05:02.260 --> 05:03.887
Generations?

05:03.970 --> 05:05.555
But it's really just a home.
It's just walls and a window--

05:05.597 --> 05:08.183
I mean, all that stuff
is long gone.

05:08.266 --> 05:10.685
I see that your rate is between
15 and 20 dollars an hour,

05:10.769 --> 05:15.273
and I-I'll pay you $200 just
to come up and-and meet the kids

05:15.357 --> 05:17.817
and tour the house.

05:17.901 --> 05:19.486
Two hundred?

05:19.569 --> 05:20.904
I will pay for your car
both ways.

05:20.945 --> 05:21.905
And just come up,

05:21.946 --> 05:23.531
and if you're not
feeling the vibe,

05:23.615 --> 05:25.867
then you'll still get paid.

05:26.951 --> 05:28.036
Got it.

05:28.078 --> 05:30.413
Okay. See you after your work.

05:50.809 --> 05:52.394
<i>Are you insane?</i>

05:52.477 --> 05:53.978
We need the money.

05:54.062 --> 05:56.773
You said
it's a slave plantation, Shay.

05:56.815 --> 05:58.692
-Need I say more?
-Was.

05:58.775 --> 06:00.735
And relax. I'm not gonna
actually take a job

06:00.819 --> 06:03.780
babysitting a bunch of
white kids at a plantation.

06:03.822 --> 06:05.240
Like, no.

06:05.323 --> 06:07.283
Then why are you going?

06:07.325 --> 06:10.328
Because I still get paid
200 bucks.

06:10.412 --> 06:12.163
How do we know
she's not a nutcase?

06:12.247 --> 06:13.832
All right, I get it.

06:13.915 --> 06:16.751
-I'll send you my location.
-Thank you.

06:17.919 --> 06:20.005
Peace.

06:21.172 --> 06:23.967
As a Black man,
I agree with the girl.

06:25.427 --> 06:27.345
What, were you eavesdropping?

06:27.387 --> 06:28.680
You guys were loud.

06:28.722 --> 06:30.682
Well, cover your ears.

06:30.765 --> 06:33.101
I'm just saying that,
uh, you know,

06:33.184 --> 06:36.855
in this climate of racial
injustice, especially down here,

06:36.896 --> 06:39.024
it's not a good look.

06:39.065 --> 06:42.819
Well, maybe you should
keep an eye on the road.

06:45.947 --> 06:47.866
Well...

06:49.034 --> 06:51.494
...racism is harder
for brothers like me.

06:51.536 --> 06:54.039
-Expectations, you know?
-How so?

06:54.122 --> 06:55.290
I can't ball.

06:55.373 --> 06:56.958
I can't dance.

06:57.042 --> 06:59.002
It's horrible.

06:59.044 --> 07:02.297
Which is why I rely on
my most charming,

07:02.380 --> 07:04.674
undeniably adorable personality.

07:04.716 --> 07:07.177
If you need a ride,
just let me know.

07:07.218 --> 07:10.889
I'll be your personal chauffeur.

07:27.072 --> 07:28.740
Check it out.

07:33.453 --> 07:35.580
Mass graves.

07:35.663 --> 07:38.249
Where they buried the slaves.

07:38.333 --> 07:41.127
Damn, they couldn't
even give us a proper burial.

08:04.901 --> 08:07.237
Boys, come inside now.

08:13.952 --> 08:17.038
Um, what's up with this kid?

08:24.671 --> 08:26.631
Andrew, now.

08:26.673 --> 08:28.967
Yeah, now, Andrew.

08:34.472 --> 08:36.433
Well...

08:36.474 --> 08:38.476
there goes massa
and her chil'ren.

08:38.560 --> 08:40.478
Shut up.

08:43.231 --> 08:45.734
Can you just...

08:45.817 --> 08:47.652
wait till I get back?

08:47.736 --> 08:49.320
Yeah. 20 minutes.

08:49.362 --> 08:51.573
Then you're on your own.

08:52.323 --> 08:53.742
Okay.

09:10.675 --> 09:13.136
Thank you for coming.

09:16.181 --> 09:17.849
Come in.

09:18.850 --> 09:20.685
I can't imagine
what it must be like for you

09:20.769 --> 09:22.896
to be in a place like this.

09:22.979 --> 09:26.024
I'm only here because
my mother is dying,

09:26.107 --> 09:29.027
and I wanted to be with her
in her final days.

09:29.069 --> 09:31.154
I'm sorry.

09:32.364 --> 09:33.948
Uh, I mean, after the upgrades,

09:34.032 --> 09:36.910
I'm not really sure what
we're gonna do with this place.

09:37.702 --> 09:39.871
It was weird growing up here.

09:39.913 --> 09:41.498
Please don't judge me.

09:42.374 --> 09:45.168
We don't get to choose
where we grow up.

09:47.003 --> 09:49.047
Let me show you the house.

10:29.462 --> 10:31.923
Mind your step.
We're renovating.

10:31.965 --> 10:33.591
We're in the electrical phase.

10:33.675 --> 10:37.971
The connections are spotty, so
it causes the lights to flicker.

10:39.973 --> 10:42.392
This is our fun little
arts and crafts project.

10:42.434 --> 10:44.728
It keeps the kids busy.

10:48.106 --> 10:50.358
My husband cannot wait
for this debacle to be over.

10:50.442 --> 10:51.818
This is not his thing.

10:51.901 --> 10:55.280
He comes and goes from L.A.

10:56.948 --> 11:00.076
But, um, let me show you
the rest of the house.

11:19.679 --> 11:20.972
That room's a mess.

11:21.056 --> 11:23.141
Haven't gotten around
to that room yet.

11:25.935 --> 11:30.440
Springfield Model 1861 rifle.

11:32.025 --> 11:34.819
These belonged to
my great-granduncle.

11:34.903 --> 11:37.405
Fought in the Civil War?

11:37.489 --> 11:39.032
Killed in action.

11:39.115 --> 11:41.659
This was taken
when his body was returned.

11:41.743 --> 11:42.660
Whoa.

11:42.744 --> 11:44.537
Mourning portrait.

11:44.621 --> 11:45.580
That's wild.

11:45.663 --> 11:47.165
It's a way to honor those

11:47.207 --> 11:49.334
that have passed on
to the other side.

11:49.376 --> 11:51.586
How do you know so much
about this stuff?

11:51.670 --> 11:55.173
-Uh, I'm an African American
studies major. -Hmm.

11:55.256 --> 11:58.259
Focus more
on the Civil War era, but...

11:58.343 --> 12:01.763
Yeah, I've only seen these
in, like, textbooks.

12:03.515 --> 12:04.516
His wife?

12:04.599 --> 12:06.184
Mm-hmm.

12:06.226 --> 12:08.353
My mother loved
to show this off.

12:08.436 --> 12:11.356
She fancied herself
on Southern tradition.

12:11.398 --> 12:14.192
I never really understood
her pride about it.

12:17.946 --> 12:19.197
The heat is insufferable
in here.

12:19.280 --> 12:22.409
-Let me get you a fan.
-Oh. Thanks.

13:38.193 --> 13:39.819
Can you hear anything?

13:39.903 --> 13:42.155
Oh.

13:42.238 --> 13:44.491
Hey, you.

13:46.618 --> 13:48.078
What's your name?

13:50.705 --> 13:52.832
I'm Shay.

13:53.625 --> 13:54.626
I'm Blair.

13:54.709 --> 13:57.128
Nice to meet you, Blair.

13:57.170 --> 13:59.964
You have such a pretty smile.

14:00.048 --> 14:01.549
Want to play hide-and-seek?

14:01.633 --> 14:04.386
There's a lot of good places
to hide in this house.

14:04.469 --> 14:06.721
Um...

14:06.805 --> 14:08.181
yeah, sure.

14:08.264 --> 14:10.266
It didn't break!

14:15.647 --> 14:16.648
Boys.

14:22.028 --> 14:23.988
What you doing there, buddy?

14:24.030 --> 14:26.574
-I'm a pirate.
-Mm.

14:26.658 --> 14:28.660
Pirates are pretty cool.

14:29.577 --> 14:31.705
What about you?
You a pirate, too?

14:31.788 --> 14:34.332
No. I-I'm just Andrew.

14:35.667 --> 14:37.002
Hey.

14:37.043 --> 14:39.087
Stop it! Stop it.

14:39.170 --> 14:40.672
-Andrew, stop.
-You know,

14:40.714 --> 14:44.634
a weapon like that is
used against brave pirates.

14:44.676 --> 14:47.095
Last one holding it
has to walk the plank.

14:47.178 --> 14:49.180
Go wash your hands!

14:53.059 --> 14:55.770
What is that?

14:55.854 --> 14:58.523
It's a, uh, branding iron.

14:58.606 --> 15:01.276
I don't know where they even
find something like this.

15:01.359 --> 15:03.862
Well, we are on a plantation.

15:03.903 --> 15:05.780
Yeah.

15:06.698 --> 15:08.908
I think they used to have
horses here maybe.

15:12.537 --> 15:15.040
With soap.

15:23.423 --> 15:24.924
Okay.

15:27.052 --> 15:29.429
Just need to get you
cleaned up, honey.

15:29.512 --> 15:31.431
Mom, it's hot.

15:32.390 --> 15:34.809
It's too hot!

15:34.893 --> 15:37.062
Okay, Mom. Okay, okay, okay.

15:37.145 --> 15:39.356
Okay.

15:40.940 --> 15:42.734
Who wants lemonade?

15:42.776 --> 15:44.402
-Oh, me.
-Me.

15:44.486 --> 15:45.862
I hate lemonade.

15:45.904 --> 15:48.406
Shay, do you want in
on this lemonade party?

15:48.490 --> 15:49.282
Yeah.

15:49.366 --> 15:51.493
That actually sounds good.

15:56.748 --> 15:58.541
They're great kids, I promise.

15:58.583 --> 15:59.501
They really are.

15:59.542 --> 16:01.920
It's just...

16:02.003 --> 16:04.923
just the move, and I've had
to drive them to the hospital.

16:04.964 --> 16:07.133
To be honest, I don't think
they really understand

16:07.217 --> 16:08.301
what's going on and...

16:08.385 --> 16:10.261
long days turn into late nights,

16:10.345 --> 16:12.764
and when I finally get them
in bed and I crash,

16:12.847 --> 16:15.016
they're up all night, just
opening and closing the doors

16:15.100 --> 16:16.601
and flushing the toilet.

16:16.685 --> 16:19.104
I mean, how many times
can one person use the bathroom?

16:20.814 --> 16:25.985
Well, I'm not really
a great sleeper, either, so...

16:26.069 --> 16:27.737
It's really tough on Andrew.

16:27.779 --> 16:30.990
He gets these nightmares.

16:34.119 --> 16:35.412
I'm sorry.

16:35.453 --> 16:38.081
I'm supposed to be
selling you on this job.

16:38.123 --> 16:41.167
Ugh. I'm not usually
such an oversharer.

16:41.251 --> 16:46.631
Uh, my mom passed
when I was younger, so I get it.

16:46.715 --> 16:48.425
It takes a toll.

16:50.385 --> 16:52.137
Here you go, as promised.

16:52.929 --> 16:54.639
Thank you.

16:54.723 --> 16:57.434
I hope it works out, because
you seem really good with kids

16:57.475 --> 17:00.395
and I think the diversity
could be good for them.

17:01.730 --> 17:04.566
I'm gonna stop talking, but I-I
really enjoyed having you here.

17:04.649 --> 17:05.650
Take care.

17:05.734 --> 17:07.235
You, too.

17:30.300 --> 17:31.843
Waited, hmm?

17:31.926 --> 17:35.096
Only 'cause you fine, girl.

18:17.389 --> 18:19.224
Shay.

18:19.307 --> 18:21.601
What are you up to?

18:21.685 --> 18:24.354
I'm just looking up stuff
on the Hopkins estate.

18:24.396 --> 18:25.730
And you wonder why

18:25.772 --> 18:28.692
you have crazy nightmares
about this stuff.

18:30.860 --> 18:33.947
I thought you weren't
taking that job.

18:34.030 --> 18:35.824
I'm not.

18:37.575 --> 18:39.953
You know what's weird, though?

18:40.036 --> 18:43.206
That you're spending
your free time reading about

18:43.248 --> 18:46.167
sugarcane crop yields
in the fall of 1859

18:46.251 --> 18:47.919
for a job you're not taking.

18:47.961 --> 18:50.046
I've looked everywhere.

18:50.088 --> 18:51.464
Like, literally everywhere,

18:51.548 --> 18:53.925
and I can't find any information
on this place.

18:54.009 --> 18:56.219
If I kidnapped people
and forced them to work for me,

18:56.261 --> 18:59.639
I don't think I'd be too eager
to write it down, personally.

18:59.723 --> 19:01.433
I'm saying, lots of money
would've come from

19:01.474 --> 19:02.892
a plantation that size.

19:02.934 --> 19:05.186
There's no way there wouldn't be
any record of it.

19:05.270 --> 19:06.771
I love you, Shay,

19:06.813 --> 19:09.816
but I cannot watch you go down
one of your loops again.

19:09.899 --> 19:11.359
Loops?

19:11.443 --> 19:13.778
I mean, sometimes you get
a little bit obsessive.

19:13.820 --> 19:16.281
You start digging into
some Civil War thing,

19:16.364 --> 19:18.783
and then after that,
things get weird.

19:18.867 --> 19:20.785
This is different.

19:22.537 --> 19:25.206
It's something about this place.

19:25.290 --> 19:28.084
I feel drawn to it.

19:29.669 --> 19:31.463
It's weird.

20:04.996 --> 20:07.248
Kill my life.

20:14.005 --> 20:16.716
- Hello.
- Hi, Shay. It's Kate.

20:16.800 --> 20:18.843
I'm so, so sorry.

20:18.885 --> 20:20.804
Wh-What is it?

20:20.845 --> 20:23.098
My mother took a turn
for the worse,

20:23.181 --> 20:26.017
and, um, she may not make it
through the night.

20:26.101 --> 20:27.936
I'm sorry to hear that.

20:28.019 --> 20:30.814
So my husband's flying in, but
he can't get here till tomorrow.

20:30.897 --> 20:34.734
Is there... is there any way you
can come and spend the night?

20:35.985 --> 20:37.320
Right now?

20:37.362 --> 20:38.863
Yeah, uh,

20:38.947 --> 20:41.282
I have to go to St. Gabriel's,
but the kids are asleep,

20:41.366 --> 20:43.785
and, um, I'll be back
tomorrow morning.

20:43.868 --> 20:46.454
Mm... um...

20:47.205 --> 20:49.541
Yeah, I'm-I'm not sure, Kate.

20:49.582 --> 20:52.502
I'll pay you $500.

20:52.544 --> 20:55.296
Please, Shay.
I have no one else to call.

21:03.388 --> 21:05.682
Where are you going this late?

21:08.393 --> 21:10.020
You're back with Will.

21:10.061 --> 21:12.063
Hell no. Please.

21:12.147 --> 21:13.815
Then where?

21:15.066 --> 21:17.193
Kate's house.

21:17.235 --> 21:18.570
Vanilla Kate?

21:18.653 --> 21:21.197
Yes, Cream Soda Jasmine.

21:21.239 --> 21:22.824
This late?

21:22.907 --> 21:26.161
It's only for a night,
and she's paying me 500 bucks.

21:26.244 --> 21:27.662
No. No.

21:27.746 --> 21:29.497
What happened to
Miss "I'm not babysitting

21:29.581 --> 21:31.458
some white kids
at a plantation"?

21:31.541 --> 21:33.293
I'm driving you.

21:33.376 --> 21:35.378
I already called a car.

21:36.588 --> 21:39.090
Seriously, dude, don't go.

21:39.132 --> 21:41.885
Girl, you only want me to stay
because you're high

21:41.926 --> 21:43.803
and too scared to watch
this movie by yourself.

21:43.887 --> 21:46.389
No, I'm just hungry.

21:47.599 --> 21:50.101
Well, there's a burrito
in the freezer.

21:50.143 --> 21:51.394
You'll be good.

21:51.436 --> 21:52.479
Bye, Jas.

21:52.562 --> 21:54.064
Okay, then I'm going with you.

21:54.105 --> 21:57.025
Kate's never met you.
She's not going for that.

21:57.108 --> 21:59.110
Okay, fine.

21:59.194 --> 22:02.781
You call me as soon as you get
there and check in with me.

22:02.822 --> 22:03.907
Okay.

22:03.948 --> 22:05.241
Don't go to sleep,

22:05.283 --> 22:08.828
and keep an eye on everyone.

22:11.414 --> 22:13.416
Anything else?

22:13.458 --> 22:15.960
Do not go in there.

22:16.002 --> 22:17.837
In where?

22:18.838 --> 22:21.216
You'll know when you see it.

22:21.299 --> 22:22.342
Oh, God. Okay.

22:22.425 --> 22:24.594
Well, bye.

22:27.222 --> 22:28.306
Mm-mm.

22:56.918 --> 22:59.462
So you're actually gonna
spend the night there?

23:00.839 --> 23:02.173
Mm-hmm.

23:02.966 --> 23:06.011
It's good money,
and I don't scare easily.

23:28.033 --> 23:31.536
Okay, well, if you need
anything, just call me.

23:31.578 --> 23:33.121
No matter what.

23:33.204 --> 23:34.372
I'm your guy.

23:34.414 --> 23:36.541
I'll be here...

23:53.558 --> 23:55.268
- Thank you for coming...
- Oh.

23:55.352 --> 23:56.394
...on such short notice.

23:56.436 --> 23:57.479
Don't worry about me.

23:57.562 --> 23:59.689
Just go be with your mom.

24:06.571 --> 24:08.907
Okay.

24:33.973 --> 24:35.934
So, keep track of
any movements by them.

24:36.017 --> 24:38.728
They should sleep through
the night, except Andrew.

24:38.770 --> 24:42.399
He randomly gets up,
like, 3:00 a.m.-ish.

24:42.440 --> 24:44.526
And like an episode
or something?

24:44.609 --> 24:46.194
No, it's-it's like
a night terror,

24:46.277 --> 24:47.529
but then it passes.

24:47.612 --> 24:49.114
It only started
when we moved here.

24:49.155 --> 24:52.117
Um, this is the police
department, fire department,

24:52.200 --> 24:54.494
and St. Gabriel's,
where I'll be.

24:54.577 --> 24:56.913
Um, here's a list
of approved snacks.

24:56.955 --> 24:59.290
